Damage Adder missing pulses<br>
Speed Song missing pulses<br>
Resist Chant spam<br>
Snare not getting aggro<br>
Misfires of Damage Shouts<br>
Battlesong Items<br>
<br>
Issues:<br>
Song of Rest<br>
RA-Fury of the Gods<br>
Endurance/Power usuage<br>
Resist Songs<br>
Damage Adder stacking<br>
<br>
Requests:<br>
Medium Shields<br>
Snare changes<br>
<br>
<br>
Bugs:<br>
<br>
Damage Adder/Speed Song missing pulses - This has been in at least the last 3 Skald reports and it really does need to be corrected. I have grouped the Adder and Speed together because they really are the same problem. We lose our Damage Adder during battle, and it has been assumed to be because the pulse for these songs is 5 seconds, while the duration of the song is 6 seconds. That leave a window of opportunity for the adder to not be counted during the lapse between duration and pulse. This happens the same way with the Speed Songs.<br>
<br>
Resist Chant Spam - We want to be able to turn off the messages from this line of chants. They are pulsed songs yet their messages are not effected by the chat option for pulsed songs.<br>
<br>
Snare not getting aggro - On occasion, if you cast your Snare Shout from a distance, the mob will not be snared, but you will use endurance and power and your timer will be reset. Not sure why this is happening, but it has been reported by a number of people.<br>
<br>
Misfires of Damage Shouts - On occasion if you cast a Damage Shout on a mob from the outer fringes or the range (Which is very small BTW) you will see the spell effect, get a message that it has been cast, but the mob takes no damage. Since the range of the Damage shouts are so small, there is no reason why we would be out of range of a resist message.<br>
<br>
Battlesong Items- After extensive testing we have come to the conclusion that Battlesong items do absolutly nothing for us. There is no effect on damage, resists, or duration. Can the Battlesong stat on items be replaced with something useful or can Battlesong stat actually have an effect?<br>
<br>
<br>
Issues:<br>
<br>
Song of Rest - By far this is the most complained about Song we have. Other than at the lowest levels, the HP return is neglible. Something needs to be done to make this song worthwhile. Suggestions on the board are either make it so that it returns more as the Song scales, or to completely change the song to a real Song of Rest, make it so that it regens HP, Power, and Endurance, but only while outside of battle. As it stands now, any Skald getting the level 50 Song of Rest gets the benefit of 12 HP per pulse (6 seconds) and only while sitting out of combat for more than 10 seconds, that means that for our top line spec song we are awarded 120 total HP regen if we sit for a full minute.<br>
<br>
RA-Fury of the Gods - If I can find one Skald who purchased this ability and actually thinks they got their money's worth then I would be amazed. By far the most complained about RA. The return on investment just doesn't exist. It needs to be changed to higher damage and have it's cost reduced, or it needs to be changed to an entirely different Realm ability.<br>
<br>
Endurance/Power usage - Our Shouts use Power, our Shouts use Endurance. Why does it have to use so much of both? Can this be changed to use less of one of those two items? At the start of any battle, if we use our shouts, we are stating with 2/3 of our endurance. Not to mention turning on our pulsed songs use endurance. I ask seriously that this gets reviewed.<br>
<br>
Resist Songs - 6 songs of nominal benefit taking up 6 slots on a hotbar with only 8 spots and uses endurance to cast? Please combine them into at least groups of 2. (And get rid of the message spam!). At least change the songs so there is a slight benefit to using them.<br>
<br>
Damage Adder Stacking - Currently when our Damage Adder is stacked, it if half our normal damage plus the stack. Since we have the better Damage Adder in Midgard, the results are always equal to or less than the Damage adder song alone. Don't halve the Skald Damage Adder and halve or 3rd the stacked adder instead so that we can see some reason for stacking. We do not have a 10.0 DPS adder as others have, and as a group we should be able to attain that level.<br>
<br>
Requests:<br>
<br>
Medium Shields - We would at least like the ability to weild medium shields even if we are unable to spec in any shield. As rare as a shield/weapon Skald is, it is still something that has been requested.<br>
<br>
Snare Changes - We would like to be able to access our lower level Snare Shouts, or at least the one prior to the current one. Snare is a power/endurance hog and all we get for getting the higher spells is a longer duration, which is not something that is needed. A Snare that lasts 1:29 is a bit too long considering the length of an average battle.<br>
<br>
